Surfaced 2026-06-09 by the containerised integration harness (clean container, no host-installed extras).

PROBLEM
DBIO::DB2::Loader does `use base qw/DBIO::Loader::DBI::Component::QuotedDefault DBIO::Loader::DBI/`. In a clean environment those base classes do not exist:
  Base class package "DBIO::Loader::DBI::Component::QuotedDefault" is empty
=> t/00-load.t fails (use_ok DBIO::DB2::Loader).

DBIO::Loader is the legacy introspection system. It is:
  - NOT in dbio core (find dbio/lib -path '*Loader*' => empty; core dropped it)
  - NOT on CPAN (cpanm --info DBIO::Loader => not found)
  - only present because it happens to be installed in the dev's ~/perl5
  - NOT declared in dbio-db2/cpanfile

Sibling drivers already moved on: dbio-postgresql and dbio-mysql have NO Loader.pm. Only dbio-db2 and dbio-sqlite still carry the legacy Loader (dbio-sqlite/t/00-load.t has the same latent failure).

DECISION NEEDED (pick one, ideally consistent with sqlite):
  (a) REMOVE DBIO::DB2::Loader + its t/00-load.t entry + CLAUDE.md "Loader" rows — match pg/mysql. New Introspect/Diff/Deploy stack replaces it.
  (b) KEEP it but declare DBIO::Loader as an optional dep and guard the load test (skip if DBIO::Loader absent). Requires DBIO::Loader to be published somewhere installable.

Recommend (a): the driver's own Introspect (SYSCAT) + Generate path is the supported route; Loader is dead weight.

Cross-ref: dbio-sqlite has the identical issue — coordinate a fleet-wide decision.
DONE 2026-06-09 (commit 1747e51): removed lib/DBIO/DB2/Loader.pm; t/00-load.t now loads real components; CLAUDE.md cleaned. Chose option (a) remove, matching pg/mysql. NOTE: dbio-sqlite has identical latent failure — needs same decision there.
